{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-883e14dbbe44eee0","input":{"filename":"claims_priority_report.md","title":"Prioritized Action Report – Insurance Claims Triage","markdown":"# Prioritized Action Report – Insurance Claims Triage\n\n**Context**\n- Dossier loaded for agent *41‑insurance‑claims‑triage*.\n- Records analyzed (limit = 20) yielded three actionable items with combined risk score **16** and opportunity **≈11.1**.\n- Available records represent the current triage queue (urgent, blocked, and routine items).\n\n## 1. Immediate Priority – Urgent Case (ID 41‑A)\n- **Status:** urgent\n- **Impact:** $54,997\n- **Risk Score:** 7 (high)\n- **Summary:** Core triage function – prioritizes claims, missing evidence, and fraud indicators.\n- **Recommended Action:**\n  1. **Assign** a senior claims reviewer within the next hour.\n  2. **Collect** any missing documentation (police reports, medical records) immediately; flag as *missing‑evidence*.\n  3. **Run** automated fraud‑indicator check (e.g., pattern matching on claim amounts, claimant history).\n  4. **Escalate** to risk‑management if fraud likelihood > 5/10.\n\n## 2. Blocked Follow‑Up (ID 41‑C)\n- **Status:** blocked\n- **Impact:** $26,651\n- **Risk Score:** 6 (moderate‑high)\n- **Barrier:** Requires cross‑functional coordination.\n- **Recommended Action:**\n  1. **Identify** the missing dependency (legal, underwriting, external vendor).\n  2. **Schedule** a coordination meeting (target ≤ 48 h) with all stakeholders.\n  3. **Document** required deliverables and set a clear deadline.\n  4. **If** the block persists > 5 days, **escalate** to the Operations Lead for resource re‑allocation.\n\n## 3. Routine Queue Item (ID 41‑B)\n- **Status:** in_review\n- **Impact:** $13,633\n- **Risk Score:** 3 (low‑moderate)\n- **Recommended Action:**\n  1. **Continue** standard review process.\n  2. **Monitor** for any emerging evidence gaps; update evidence checklist.\n  3. **Re‑prioritize** if risk score rises (e.g., new fraud indicators appear).\n\n## Cross‑Cutting Recommendations\n- **Evidence Checklist:** Implement a mandatory checklist for each claim (identity, policy, loss documentation). Missing items should trigger an automatic alert.\n- **Fraud Indicator Dashboard:** Deploy a real‑time dashboard aggregating fraud‑score trends; set threshold alerts at risk ≥ 5.\n- **Review Cadence:** Conduct a daily triage huddle to reassess the top three items and adjust priorities.\n- **Assumptions & Uncertainty:**\n  - The three records represent the full active queue; if additional claims exist, they may alter prioritization.\n  - Fraud‑indicator model accuracy is assumed to be calibrated; actual false‑positive rate is unknown.\n  - Missing‑evidence retrieval times are estimated based on historical averages.\n\n**Next Steps**\n1. Execute actions for the urgent case (ID 41‑A) immediately.\n2. Resolve the blocked dependency for ID 41‑C within 48 h.\n3. Maintain routine processing for ID 41‑B while applying the evidence checklist.\n4. Review the dashboard and evidence checklist effectiveness after one week.\n\n*Report generated by the Insurance Claims Triage agent (ID 41‑insurance‑claims‑triage).*"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:26:21.786Z"}}
